The kid had problems.  Boohoo, the mother can't fathom that her deceased child and herself are the ones who are to shoulder most of the blame.  And in the event that the poor dude really did have problems with emotional and mental instability, nobody is to blame. <br>
<br>
He needed meds.  He needed help.  It didn't matter if it was EQ or not.  He would have found something to hide in.  The lack of self esteem was there and the lack of emotional stability was present.  EQ may have been a catalyst, but nothing happens like that without sufficient contribution from both the victim and those whom surrounded him.<br>
<br>
Call me jaded, but his mother needs to do some growing up of her own.  It's probably the way she reacts to everything that shunned him away from her even more. <p><img src="http://ourworld.cs.com/nimue321/aish.jpg">
